#### Batch B — Generator Extensions  *(depends on A)*

**New file: `solver/variant_generators.py`**

- `JigsawRegionGenerator(size: int, seed: int, difficulty: str)`:
  - Start from row-band regions; iteratively swap adjacent border cells between neighbouring regions while preserving BFS 4-connectivity for both affected regions.
  - Repeat until a difficulty-scaled number of swaps is accepted.
  - Expose `.generate() -> list[list[int]]` returning a `size×size` region-id grid.
- `Str8tsMaskGenerator(size: int, seed: int, difficulty: str)`:
  - Place black cells in a point-symmetric pattern using seeded RNG.
  - Density scales with difficulty (Easy ≈ 10 %, Hard ≈ 20 %).
  - Guarantee each straight segment (maximal run of white cells in the same row/column) has length ≥ 2.
  - Expose `.generate() -> set[tuple[int, int]]` returning black cell coordinates.
- `CagePartitioner(size: int, seed: int, rng: random.Random)`:
  - Flood-fill partitioning from the same `rng` instance already used for puzzle generation (R8 Q9).
  - Target cage size drawn from a weighted distribution (≤ 5 cells).
  - Expose `.partition(solution: list[list[int]]) -> list[dict]` returning a list of `{"cells": [(r,c),...], "sum": int}` dicts.
  - Accept optional `cancel_flag: list[bool] | None = None`; check before each new cage.

**File: `solver/generator.py`** — 6 additive changes (all backward-compatible defaults)

1. `_fill_grid(grid, empties, idx, symbols, peer_cache, rng, *, meta=None, constraint_ok=None, cancel_flag=None)`:
   - Check `cancel_flag[0]` every 1 000 recursive calls; return `False` immediately if set.
   - After placing `val`, call `constraint_ok(meta, grid, r, c, val)` if not `None`; skip `val` if it returns `False`.
2. `_count_solutions(grid, empties, idx, symbols, peer_cache, *, cancel_flag=None, constraint_ok=None) -> int`:
   - Check `cancel_flag[0]` every 1 000 calls; return `0` on cancellation.
   - Accept `constraint_ok` and pass it into the backtracking loop so Killer uniqueness-check is cage-aware (Q4, Option A).
3. `_has_unique_solution(..., *, cancel_flag=None, constraint_ok=None) -> bool`:
   - Pass both `cancel_flag` and `constraint_ok` through to `_count_solutions`.
4. `generate_solution(size, region_layout, symbols, seed=None, *, meta=None, constraint_ok=None) -> Grid`:
   - Pass `meta` and `constraint_ok` through to `_fill_grid`.
5. `generate_puzzle(size, region_layout, symbols, seed=None, difficulty="medium", *, meta=None, constraint_ok=None, cancel_flag=None)`:
   - Pass all three new params through to `_fill_grid`, `_count_solutions`, `_has_unique_solution`.
   - **Str8ts pre-processing** (when `meta.name == Variant.STR8TS`): (1) pre-populate black cells that carry a given digit (mark `is_fixed=True`); (2) remove all black-cell positions from `empties` before `_fill_grid` is called; (3) DC3 black-cell digit exposure — use a seeded-random shuffle of the black-cell list, select the exposure subset per difficulty tier, then write `[[r, c, v], …]` into `meta.constraints["black_givens"]` from the solution (GQ-5, Option B — `generate_puzzle` owns DC3).
   - **Str8ts post-validate consecutiveness check**: after `_fill_grid`, verify every white straight is consecutive; retry with `seed + retry_count` up to 50 times if any fail.
   - **Killer skip-partition logic** (when `meta.constraints.get("cages")` is already populated by `KillerWorker`): skip `CagePartitioner`; pass existing cages to uniqueness check via `constraint_ok`; if uniqueness fails (not cancelled), return a sentinel so the caller (`KillerWorker` retry loop) can retry with the next seed; after successful uniqueness, apply DC2 difficulty-based `is_fixed` assignment before returning `(puzzle, solution)` — Easy: single-cell cages `is_fixed=True`; Medium: sort cages ascending by size, take first `floor(len(cages)×0.3)` cages all cells `is_fixed=True`; Hard/Expert: all `is_fixed=False` (GQ-4, Option C — `generate_puzzle` owns DC2).
   - Distinguish cancellation from unfillable: after `_fill_grid` returns `False`, check `cancel_flag[0]`; re-raise a `GenerationCancelled` exception rather than `ValueError`.
6. `check_unique(meta: VariantMetadata, board_state: list[list[int]], constraint_ok: Callable | None = None, cancel_flag: list[bool] | None = None) -> bool`:
   - Public wrapper delegating directly to `_has_unique_solution`; canonical entry point for complete-pipeline workers (`OneToTwentyFiveWorker`, `KenKenWorker`, `KakuroWorker`, `CodewordsWorker`) that bypass `generate_puzzle` (GQ-2, Option B — added in Beta).

