## Round 8 Decisions (R8)

| Q | Topic | Decision |
|---|-------|----------|
| R8 Q1 | `VariantMetadata` partial-stub sentinel | A — `__post_init__` treats `region_layout = []` as valid sentinel; worker replaces in-place; non-empty layouts validated as before |
| R8 Q2 | `new_game` hint-limit parameter | A — fourth keyword param: `new_game(meta, difficulty, seed=None, hint_limit: int | None = 3)`; `None` = unlimited |
| R8 Q3 | Str8ts mask ownership | A — `Str8tsWorker` calls `Str8tsMaskGenerator`, writes result into `meta.constraints["black_cells"]`, then passes `meta` to `generate_puzzle`; generator only reads |
| R8 Q4 | Hint limit unlimited sentinel | A — `None` = unlimited; positive `int` = cap; persisted as `"hint_limit": null` or `"hint_limit": N` |
| R8 Q5 | Hint mode selection mechanism | A — `hint(mode: str)` receives mode on each call; `MainWindow` passes from persistent UI toggle (radio/combo) |
| R8 Q6 | Conflict highlight scope | A — board-wide: replace `_conflict_cells(board, sel, ...)` with `_all_conflict_cells(board, size, region_layout)` scanning all pairs; both cells in every conflict highlighted regardless of selection |
| R8 Q7 | Arrow key boundary behaviour | A — **stop** at grid boundary (no wrap); Tab/Shift-Tab continues to wrap row-major |
| R8 Q8 | Str8ts candidate filter algorithm | A — exact per-candidate test via shared `_can_extend_straight(placed, length, v) -> bool` helper; used by both `update_all_candidates` and `_Str8tsRun` SE technique |
| R8 Q9 | Killer cage RNG seeding | A — single `random.Random(puzzle_seed)` used in sequence for fill → partition → clue removal; no separate cage salt or `cage_seed` |
| R8 Q10 | Text format structure | A — header block (`variant`, `size`, `seed`, `difficulty`) then digit rows (`0` = empty); variant-specific fields as extra header lines |

## Round 9 Decisions (R9)

| Q | Topic | Decision |
|---|-------|----------|
| R9 Q1 | Worker scope Str8ts/Killer | B — workers do only slow variant-specific step; `Str8tsWorker` writes mask → emits `finished(meta)`; `KillerWorker` writes cages → emits `finished(meta)`; `generate_puzzle` called by `new_game` on main thread |
| R9 Q2 | Seed pre-generation | A — `MainWindow._on_new_game` picks seed before dialog; passes as `initial_seed`; uses same value in `new_game(meta, difficulty, seed=initial_seed, ...)` |
| R9 Q3 | Hint mode Beta completeness | A — all 4 modes implemented: `auto_fill` (fill+lock 1, decrements); `show_candidate` (reveal, no fill, no decrement); `multi_reveal` (fill+lock 3, decrements); `walkthrough` (SE-guided highlight, no fill, no decrement) |
| R9 Q4 | End-of-game dialog | A — custom `GameCompleteDialog(QDialog)` with `QVBoxLayout`; three `QPushButton` objects; result codes `OK`/`NEW_GAME`/`RESTART`; `MainWindow._on_game_complete` inspects result |
| R9 Q5 | Hint mode selector widget | C — `QButtonGroup` of 4 radio buttons added as widget in status bar; `MainWindow` stores `_hint_mode: str` |
| R9 Q6 | hint_limit schema version | A — no bump; `_serialize` writes `"hint_limit": null/N`; `_deserialize` uses `data.get("hint_limit", 3)`; `SaveState` gains `hint_limit: int | None = 3`; schema stays v2 |
| R9 Q7 | EXTENDED migration | A — silent substitution in both `from_dict` methods: `"extended"` → `"1to25"` before `Variant(...)`; no `DeprecationWarning`; no schema bump |
| R9 Q8 | Arrow navigation structure | B — extract `_move_selection(dr: int, dc: int) -> None` from `keyPressEvent`; clamp + black-cell scan; `_advance_selection` gains `skip_black: bool = True`; all arrow-key logic delegates to `_move_selection` |
| R9 Q9 | Conflict highlight gate | A — `_all_conflict_cells` computed unconditionally when `meta is not None`; always visible regardless of selection; pre-existing conflicts visible on first render |

